{
  "local_port": 36700,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the postings under SSC?",
  "response": "The Staff Selection Commission (SSC) conducts various exams to recruit staff for different positions across ministries, departments, and organizations of the Government of India. Some of the prominent postings under SSC include:\n\n1. **SSC Combined Graduate Level (CGL) Exam**:\n   - Assistant Audit Officer\n   - Assistant Accounts Officer\n   - Assistant Section Officer\n   - Inspector of Income Tax\n   - Inspector (Central Excise)\n   - Inspector (Preventive Officer)\n   - Inspector (Examiner)\n   - Assistant Enforcement Officer\n   - Sub Inspector (Central Bureau of Investigation)\n   - Inspector Posts (Department of Post)\n   - Auditor (Offices under C&AG, CGDA, CGA, etc.)\n   - Divisional Accountant\n\n2. **SSC Combined Higher Secondary Level (CHSL) Exam**:\n   - Lower Division Clerk (LDC)\n   - Junior Secretariat Assistant (JSA)\n   - Postal Assistant/Sorting Assistant\n   - Data Entry Operator (DEO)\n\n3. **SSC Multi Tasking Staff (MTS) Exam**:\n   - Multi Tasking Staff (Non-Technical)\n\n4. **SSC Junior Engineer (JE) Exam**:\n   - Junior Engineer (Civil, Electrical, Mechanical, and Quantity Surveying & Contracts) in different organizations/department\n\n5. **SSC Stenographer Grade 'C' and 'D' Exam**:\n   - Stenographer Grade 'C'\n   - Stenographer Grade 'D'\n\n6. **SSC Sub-Inspector in CPOs Exam**:\n   - Sub-Inspector in Delhi Police\n   - Sub-Inspector in Central Armed Police Forces (CAPFs)\n\n7. **SSC Constable (GD) in CAPFs, NIA, SSF, and Rifleman (GD) in Assam Rifles Exam**:\n   - Constable (GD)\n   - Rifleman (GD)\n\nThese positions offer various roles across different levels of responsibility and complexity, catering to candidates with different educational qualifications and skill sets. The SSC exams are competitive, and candidates are selected based on their performance in a tiered examination process.",
